HEADWORD: Sheeps-foot
<hw>Sheep's-foot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A printer's tool
consisting of a metal bar formed into a hammer head at one end and a
claw at the other, -- used as a lever and hammer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

